# Fitting the Model in R

The basic R function is `lm()`:


::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
lm(response ~ predictor, data = df)
```
:::


For the sparrow example:


::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
sparrow_mod <- lm(wing ~ age, data = sparrows)
summary(sparrow_mod)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
